This example follow an homogeneous collapse assuming the existence of a quantum pressure. 
To generate the initial conditions locally, if pNbody is installed, run:

./makeICs.py


To run this example with the ULDM SPH solver, SWIFT must be configured with the following options:

./configure --with-hydro="uldm"

To start the simulation:

./run.sh

To show the evolution of the model mass profile:

plotSphericalProfile -y density  --xmin 0  --xmax 0.3 --rmax 0.3 --nr 128 --remove_ic_shift snap/snapshot*.hdf5 --log y 


